{"cursor":"6988","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{|{{Infobox Aircraft Begin |name= Aerion SBJ |image= Aerion SBJ.jpg |caption=\nArtist's rendering of Aerion SBJ in flight }}{{Infobox Aircraft Type |type=\nSupersonic business jet |manufacturer= Aerion Corporation |first flight=\n|introduced= |retired= |status= Under development |primary user= |more users=\n|produced= |number built= |unit cost= US$80 million (target cost) |variants with\ntheir own articles= }}\n|}\nThe 'Aerion SBJ' is a concept for a supersonic business jet, designed by Aerion\nCorporation, an American aerospace firm based in Reno, Nevada. If produced, it\nwould allow practical non-stop travel from Europe to North America and back\nwithin one business day. The target price is $80 million (in 2007 year dollars),\nwith development costs ranging from $2.5 to $3.0 billion, and is set to be\nproduced in 2015. ExecuJet of Switzerland and Indigo Lyon are the firm's sales\nagents worldwide, with the exception of North America. [http://www.bartintl.com/headlines/mar-2012/indigo-lyon-selected-\nsales-representative-aerion-sbj Indigo Lyon Selected as Sales Representative for\nAerion SBJ, BARTIntl.com, 3/14/12] The company claims 50 letters-of-intent\nfrom customers, {{cite web|url=http://www.flightglobal.com/articles/2010/10/18/348365/nbaa-aerion-\ngets-supersonic-test-results.html |accessdate=2010-10-18 |author=Doyle, Andrew\n|title=NBAA: Aerion gets supersonic test results\n| archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20101101091209/http://www.flightglobal-\n| .com/articles/2010/10/18/348365/nbaa-aerion-gets-supersonic-test-results.html|\n| archivedate= 1 November 2010 | deadurl= no}} each with a\n| $250,000 deposit. [http://www.aerioncorp.com/aerion-update-report Press\n| Releases] Entry into service is expected to take place around 2017/18\n| following the formation of a joint venture and \"hard launch\"\n| decision. Pawlowski, A.\n| [http://www.cnn.com/2009/TRAVEL/06/18/supersonic.flight.fu